<item>
            <title>[SOLR-1348] JdbcDataSource does not import Blob values correctly by default</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1348</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When blob values are returned through a java ResultSet Object they have the type byte[]. &lt;br/&gt;
As byte[] doesn&apos;t have a useful toString method we end up with a reference type value added to the solr document (i.e. [B@1f23c5). &lt;br/&gt;
The problem is easy to remedy by adding the attribute &apos;convertType=&quot;true&quot;&apos; to the dataSource tag within data-config.xml.&lt;br/&gt;
However this attribute does not appear to be documented anywhere and I was only able to find it after a few hours digging through the source code. &lt;br/&gt;
A simple fix for this would be to change the default value of convertType to true within the JdbcDataSource class. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
